description:
Jogger Jill,

Archie takes up jogging through Pickins' Park, and meets a beautiful but unsmiling girl who warns him to be careful at the dangerous "Coffin Curve" at the bottom of Thrill Hill.

Operation Vacation!,

Mr. Weatherbee tries to get away for a Hawaiian vacation without Archie tagging along, but the Archies are playing a gig in the same hotel he's staying in.

Vacation Deflation

On the way back from Hawaii, Mr. Weatherbee has to sit next to Archie on the plane.

description: Steel Sterling in "The Man of Steel" – To battle the forces of evil, one needs to have the fortitude of steel! Witness the origin of John "Jack" Sterling's superpowers along with his first heroic mission. A murderous bank robbery has led to the discovery of a master criminal known as The Black Knight! Steel Sterling must take down a castle full of thugs to end the deadly thief's reign. Will his first valiant undertaking be his last?

description: Steel Sterling in “The Return of the Black Knight” – A massive prison break is only the beginning of Jack Sterling’s latest escapade! Guards struggle to keep the convicts in their cells, as our hero of steel tracks a gang of felons to Alaska. The Black Knight resurfaces as the real threat—with his eyes set on a boatload of gold. Sterling battles his way into the master criminal’s iceberg base, but finds a number of traps waiting for him. Can he bring this group to justice?

Steel Sterling in “The Black Knight’s War on Brazoria” – Under the guise of “Dr. Yar,” Sterling’s greatest foe returns to take control of an entire country. The man as sturdy as steel hopes to rescue an American scientist while also protecting the population of Brazoria. Black Knight may look different, but his devious mind continues to create weapons and monsters capable of stopping any hero! With all of these obstacles standing in the way, can Sterling beat the master criminal again?

Steel Sterling in “The Radium Robbers” – John Sterling, P.I. looks to clear Walter Cummings of chemical theft, but might need fortitude of steel to bring the true criminals to justice! The Radium King has stolen the nation’s supply of his namesake, and is holding out for a massive ransom! Sterling is willingly captured in an effort to meet this “king” face-to-face—only to find a shocking revelation! What is the true identity of this criminal?
Last issue to contain either Kalthar the giant man king of the jungle, or Mr. Satan, nether character has been used by anyone or been reprinted.
Notes: This issue features the first appearance of Wilbur Wilkin.
